Thanks, Bruce.  

Your recordings are fantastic, so what works for you, you should stay 
with. :) I was wondering what others encountered by doing this.  I 
added headphones and a mic to pick up my voice, so I can do sessions 
without speakers.  I&#39;ll let you know if it is better for me next week.

LC

--- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, bruce halliday 
&lt;paranormalinvestigating@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt; 
&gt; LC,
&gt;  
&gt; I don&#39;t directly record from any box that I use
&gt; for the simple reason that I want to hear the live responses from 
the box
&gt; in real time.
&gt;  
&gt; this can be achieved using a splitter with the main end connected 
to the 
&gt; box and then connecting a dvr to one input and a speaker or 
headphones to the other.
&gt;  
&gt; I personally do not like to hook anything up to the box also 
because I believe that any other device
&gt; that is hooked into the box directly can interfere or even dampen 
the signal being received.
&gt;  
&gt; But I guess the main reason is, the way I do and record a session 
is the way I learned too
&gt; and it&#39;s hard to teach an old dog new tricks.
&gt;  
